---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Privacy Policy — Dr. Sébastien Delhasse" description="Privacy policy and personal data protection for drdelhasse-cardiologue.ch" lang="en">

  <section class="hero-page">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>Privacy <span class="text-primary">Policy</span></h1>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section legal">
    <div class="container legal-content">
      <p>Protecting your personal data and respecting medical confidentiality are priorities for Dr Sébastien Delhasse. This policy describes how we collect, use and protect your data, in accordance with the Federal Act on Data Protection (FADP).</p>

      <h2>1. Data controller</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Name:</strong> Dr Sébastien Delhasse</li>
        <li><strong>Company:</strong> CABINET MÉDICAL DELHASSE Sébastien Sàrl</li>
        <li><strong>Address:</strong> Route de la Bonne-Eau 18, 3960 Sierre, Valais, Switzerland</li>
        <li><strong>Email:</strong> sebastien.delhasse@hotmail.com</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>2. Data collected</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Data provided voluntarily:</strong> name, surname, email address, telephone number, message content and attachments via the contact form. Medical data is only processed with your explicit consent.</li>
        <li><strong>Data collected automatically:</strong> IP address, browser type, pages visited, visit duration (via analytical cookies if you consent).</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>3. Purposes and legal bases</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Management of contact and appointment requests — <em>performance of a public interest mission</em> (art. 6 FADP).</li>
        <li>Improvement of user experience and site performance — <em>consent for non-essential cookies</em> (art. 13 FADP).</li>
        <li>Compliance with legal and regulatory obligations (archiving of medical data).</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>4. Retention period</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Contact data:</strong> retained for 10 years, in accordance with medical obligations.</li>
        <li><strong>Analytical cookies:</strong> retained for 13 months then automatically purged.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>5. Recipients</h2>
      <p>Data may be shared with:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Our technical service providers (host, CRM solutions, etc.), all bound by a confidentiality obligation.</li>
        <li>Competent authorities in the event of a legal or judicial request.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>6. Transfers outside Switzerland</h2>
      <p>Data is primarily hosted in Switzerland. If a third-party provider stores your data in the European Union, standard GDPR safeguards apply.</p>

      <h2>7. Security</h2>
      <p>Technical measures (SSL/TLS encryption, firewalls) and organisational measures (restricted access, regular backups) ensure the protection of your data.</p>

      <h2>8. Your rights</h2>
      <p>Under the FADP, you may exercise:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Right of access, rectification or deletion of your data.</li>
        <li>Right to restriction or objection to processing.</li>
        <li>Right to data portability (where applicable).</li>
        <li>Right to withdraw your consent to analytical cookies at any time.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>To exercise your rights, write to us at <a href="mailto:sebastien.delhasse@hotmail.com">sebastien.delhasse@hotmail.com</a> or by post to the office address.</p>

      <h2>9. Updates</h2>
      <p>This policy may be modified at any time.</p>
      <p><strong>Last updated:</strong> 20 June 2025.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>

<style>
  .hero-page { background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--color-navy) 0%, #1a3d6d 100%); padding: 6rem 0 4rem; color: var(--color-white); }
  .hero-page h1 { color: var(--color-white); font-size: 2.75rem; }
  .legal-content { max-width: 800px; }
  .legal-content h2 { margin-top: 2.5rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; font-size: 1.25rem; }
  .legal-content ul { margin-bottom: 1rem; padding-left: 1.5rem; }
  .legal-content li { list-style: disc; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; color: var(--color-gray); font-size: 0.95rem; }
  .legal-content a { color: var(--color-primary); font-weight: 600; }
  @media (max-width: 768px) { .hero-page h1 { font-size: 2rem; } }
</style>
